13/03/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Parliament adopted the Law on Ministries on Friday (March 11th) that will streamline the government, reducing the number of ministries from 24 to 17, and the number of members from 27 to 21.
Parliament Speaker Slavica Djukic-Dejanovic said on Friday that Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic has already forwarded his nominees for new ministers to parliament.
She will schedule a session for Monday to discuss the proposed government reshuffle and the election of new ministers.
Earlier on Friday, 14 ministers forwarded their resignations from the government.
(B92, Tanjug, RTS - 11/03/11)
